{
  "version": "2.1.0",
  "$schema": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/oasis-tcs/sarif-spec/master/Schemata/sarif-schema-2.1.0.json",
  "runs": [
    {
      "tool": {
        "driver": {
          "name": "Tachi",
          "semanticVersion": "1.1",
          "informationUri": "https://github.com/david-matousek/tachi",
          "rules": [
            {
              "id": "tachi/stride/spoofing",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "Identity spoofing threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Components vulnerable to identity spoofing — attackers impersonating legitimate users, services, or agents to gain unauthorized access. Covers session hijacking, credential forgery, service impersonation, and agent identity spoofing in multi-agent architectures." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review authentication mechanisms at all trust boundary crossings. Check for mutual TLS, signed tokens, and replay prevention.",
                "markdown": "**Detection guidance**: Review authentication at trust boundaries. Check for mTLS, signed tokens, MFA, replay prevention.\n\n**References**: OWASP A07:2021 (Identification and Authentication Failures), CWE-287 (Improper Authentication), MITRE ATT&CK T1078 (Valid Accounts)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "stride", "spoofing", "authentication", "identity"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/stride/tampering",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "Data tampering threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Components vulnerable to unauthorized data modification — tampering with messages, data stores, model inputs, training data, or configuration. Covers in-transit tampering, data poisoning, context window injection, and training signal manipulation." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review integrity controls: digital signatures, HMAC, append-only stores, and input validation.",
                "markdown": "**Detection guidance**: Review integrity controls at data sources and transit paths. Check for message signing, HMAC, Merkle trees on log stores.\n\n**References**: OWASP A03:2021 (Injection), CWE-345 (Insufficient Verification of Data Authenticity), OWASP LLM03:2025 (Training Data Poisoning)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "stride", "tampering", "integrity", "data-poisoning"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/stride/repudiation",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "Repudiation threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Components where actions can be denied — insufficient logging, missing non-repudiation controls, or tamper-evident audit trail gaps. Covers agent action repudiation, model update attribution failures, and delivery confirmation gaps." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review audit logging completeness, log integrity, and non-repudiation mechanisms.",
                "markdown": "**Detection guidance**: Review audit logging for completeness and tamper-evidence. Check for signed log entries, monotonic sequence numbers, and atomic write-before-action semantics.\n\n**References**: OWASP A09:2021 (Security Logging and Monitoring Failures), CWE-778 (Insufficient Logging)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "stride", "repudiation", "audit", "logging"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/stride/information-disclosure",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "Information disclosure threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Components that may leak sensitive information — context window leakage, corpus exfiltration, log exposure, model memorization, and inter-agent message interception. Covers both intentional and inadvertent disclosure paths." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review data classification, access controls, output scrubbing, and encryption at rest and in transit.",
                "markdown": "**Detection guidance**: Review output scrubbing before external responses. Check access controls on logs and data stores. Verify inter-agent message encryption.\n\n**References**: OWASP A01:2021 (Broken Access Control), CWE-200 (Exposure of Sensitive Information to an Unauthorized Actor), OWASP LLM06:2025 (Sensitive Information Disclosure)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "stride", "information-disclosure", "data-exposure", "encryption"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/stride/denial-of-service",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "Denial of service threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Components vulnerable to resource exhaustion or availability degradation — rate limiting gaps, queue flooding, connection pool exhaustion, and runaway processing. Covers both external DoS and internal agent-driven resource competition." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review rate limiting, resource budgets, circuit breakers, and backpressure mechanisms.",
                "markdown": "**Detection guidance**: Review rate limiting at all ingress points. Check for circuit breakers, resource quotas, and queue depth limits.\n\n**References**: OWASP A04:2021 (Insecure Design — resource constraints), CWE-400 (Uncontrolled Resource Consumption), CWE-770 (Allocation of Resources Without Limits)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "stride", "denial-of-service", "availability", "rate-limiting"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/stride/elevation-of-privilege",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "Privilege escalation threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Components where attackers can gain capabilities beyond their authorized scope — prompt injection enabling self-authorization, forged delegation messages, Guardrails bypass, and model update compromise giving model-parameter control." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review authorization at all privilege boundaries. Check for per-session scoped permissions, independent downstream enforcement, and zero-trust tool authorization.",
                "markdown": "**Detection guidance**: Review authorization at privilege boundaries. Verify independent per-session scope enforcement at Tool Server and KB. Check for step-up auth on high-privilege operations.\n\n**References**: OWASP A01:2021 (Broken Access Control), CWE-269 (Improper Privilege Management), OWASP LLM01:2025 (Prompt Injection → privilege escalation)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "stride", "elevation-of-privilege", "authorization", "access-control"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/ai/agentic-threats",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "AI agent autonomy and misuse threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats specific to agentic AI systems — unauthorized autonomous actions, agent collusion, tool call injection, agent-in-the-middle attacks, and temporal autonomy expansion via training cycles. Covers OWASP Agentic Security Initiative (ASI) and MCP Top 10 threat categories." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review agent action scopes, tool invocation controls, inter-agent authentication, and capability auditing.",
                "markdown": "**Detection guidance**: Review agent action scope enforcement. Check for tool allowlists, parameter validation at Tool Server, capability auditing on model updates.\n\n**References**: OWASP ASI-01 (Excessive Autonomy), MCP-03 (Tool Call Injection), MITRE ATLAS AML.T0058-AML.T0062 (Agentic techniques), CSA MAESTRO (February 2025)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "ai", "agentic", "autonomy", "tool-use", "mcp"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/ai/llm-threats",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "LLM-specific threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats targeting large language models — direct and indirect prompt injection, training data poisoning, model theft, and improper output handling (OWASP LLM05:2025). Covers both input-side (prompt injection) and output-side (XSS, SQLi, SSRF) attack surfaces." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review prompt isolation, training data provenance, output encoding, and model extraction defenses.",
                "markdown": "**Detection guidance**: Review prompt architecture for instruction boundary enforcement. Verify training data provenance attestation. Check output encoding before execution sinks.\n\n**References**: OWASP LLM01:2025 (Prompt Injection), OWASP LLM03:2025 (Training Data Poisoning), OWASP LLM05:2025 (Improper Output Handling), OWASP LLM10:2025 (Model Theft), CWE-79, CWE-89, CWE-78, CWE-918"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "ai", "llm", "prompt-injection", "output-handling", "data-poisoning"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "results": [
        {
          "ruleId": "tachi/stride/spoofing",
          "message": { "text": "An attacker may impersonate a legitimate user by replaying stolen session tokens or forging identity credentials to bypass authentication at the User→Guardrails boundary.", "markdown": "Implement short-lived JWT or session tokens with binding to client IP/device fingerprint. Enforce MFA for all user sessions. Use token revocation lists and refresh-token rotation with binding checks." },
          "level": "error",
          "locations": [{ "physicalLocation": { "artifactLocation": { "uri": "examples/agentic-app/architecture.md" }, "region": { "startLine": 1 } }, "logicalLocations": [{ "name": "User", "fullyQualifiedName": "User Zone/User", "kind": "external-entity" }] }],
          "partialFingerprints": { "primaryLocationLineHash": "a1b2c3d4e5f60001", "findingId/v1": "S-1" },
          "properties": { "tags": ["security", "stride", "spoofing", "maestro-layer:L7", "maestro-pattern:trust_exploitation"], "maestro-layer": "L7 — Agent Ecosystem", "delta_status": "UNCHANGED" }
        },
        {
          "ruleId": "tachi/stride/spoofing",
          "message": { "text": "An attacker may spoof the Guardrails Service by sending crafted requests directly to the LLM Agent Orchestrator's internal endpoint, bypassing validation entirely.", "markdown": "Enforce mutual TLS (mTLS) between Guardrails Service and LLM Agent Orchestrator. Use service mesh identity (e.g., SPIFFE/SPIRE) to authenticate intra-zone service-to-service calls." },
          "level": "error",
          "locations": [{ "physicalLocation": { "artifactLocation": { "uri": "examples/agentic-app/architecture.md" }, "region": { "startLine": 1 } }, "logicalLocations": [{ "name": "Guardrails Service", "fullyQualifiedName": "Application Zone/Guardrails Service", "kind": "process" }] }],
          "partialFingerprints": { "primaryLocationLineHash": "a1b2c3d4e5f60002", "findingId/v1": "S-2" },
          "properties": { "tags": ["security", "stride", "spoofing", "maestro-layer:L6"], "maestro-layer": "L6 — Security and Compliance", "delta_status": "UNCHANGED" }
        },
        {
          "ruleId": "tachi/stride/spoofing",
          "message": { "text": "The Orchestrator's identity is not cryptographically attested to the Specialist Agent via the Inter-Agent Communication Channel, enabling rogue process injection of unauthorized delegation instructions.", "markdown": "Authenticate all Orchestrator→Channel messages using HMAC or asymmetric signing with per-session keys. The Specialist Agent MUST verify the signature before acting on delegated tasks." },
          "level": "error",
          "locations": [{ "physicalLocation": { "artifactLocation": { "uri": "examples/agentic-app/architecture.md" }, "region": { "startLine": 1 } }, "logicalLocations": [{ "name": "LLM Agent Orchestrator", "fullyQualifiedName": "Application Zone/LLM Agent Orchestrator", "kind": "process" }] }],
          "partialFingerprints": { "primaryLocationLineHash": "a1b2c3d4e5f60003", "findingId/v1": "S-3" },
          "properties": { "tags": ["security", "stride", "spoofing", "maestro-layer:L1", "maestro-pattern:trust_exploitation"], "maestro-layer": "L1 — Foundation Model", "delta_status": "UNCHANGED" }
        },
        {
          "ruleId": "tachi/stride/spoofing",
          "message": { "text": "The Specialist Agent may impersonate the Orchestrator when returning results to the Inter-Agent Communication Channel, enabling fabricated aggregated results.", "markdown": "Sign all Specialist→Channel messages with the Specialist's own identity key. The Orchestrator MUST verify the result's origin before incorporating it." },
          "level": "error",
